*Weekly Digest*


This week's updates focus on operational resilience and user experience
improvements across rider, customer, and order management workflows. We've
added safeguards to prevent critical state inconsistencies, enhanced
visibility of key order information across touchpoints, and optimized our
allocation engine to reduce friction. These changes collectively improve
order lifecycle integrity, reduce manual interventions, and create a more
seamless experience for riders and customers alike.
What=E2=80=99s New



Rider Logout Restriction During Active Tasks

A validation has been introduced to prevent riders from being logged out
while they are actively engaged in a task.


Behaviour

When a user attempts to log out a rider who is currently assigned to an
active task, the system will block the action and display an error popup
informing the user that the rider cannot be logged out until the active
task is completed.


Benefit

   -

   Prevents accidental rider logout during ongoing deliveries
   -

   Maintains task continuity and operational visibility
   -

   Reduces disruption to active order fulfillment



COD Order State Protection After Payment Collection

Additional safeguards have been implemented for Cash on Delivery (COD)
orders once the COD amount has been marked as collected.


Previous Behaviour

Orders with COD already collected could still be marked as *Failed* or
*Undelivered*, creating inconsistencies between payment collection and
delivery status.


Updated Behaviour

Once the COD status is marked as *Collected*:

   -

   Orders can no longer be marked as *Failed* or *Undelivered*
   -

   Failure and undelivered actions are restricted for both admin and rider
   workflows where applicable
   -

   The order state is protected from invalid status transitions
   -

   Only valid terminal delivery outcomes are allowed


Benefit

   -

   Prevents financial reconciliation mismatches
   -

   Ensures consistency between payment and delivery status
   -

   Reduces risk of COD-related accounting errors
   -

   Minimizes manual operational corrections and investigations
   -

   Improves overall order lifecycle integrity



Amazon Self-Ship ID Visibility

The AmazonSelfShip ID was previously visible only during the *Shipped* and =
*AWB
Manifested* stages. Once an order was completed, users could no longer
access this information from the order details, often requiring support
intervention to retrieve it.



The *AmazonSelfShip ID* will now be displayed within the *Order Details
modal* for Completed orders under the *Channel* section.


Benefit

   -

   Provides consistent visibility of AmazonSelfShip ID across all relevant
   order states.
   -

   Eliminates dependency on support teams for ID retrieval after order
   completion.
   -

   Improves operational efficiency and auditability.
   -

   Creates a unified experience across Shipped, AWB Manifested, and
   Completed order views.


Ref ID Replaces PBID in SMS Communications

To make order references more meaningful and easier to track, SMS
notifications will now display the Reference ID (Ref ID) instead of the
PBID.


Key Updates

   -

   Replaced PBID with Ref ID in customer SMS communications.
   -

   Users can now identify and reference their orders using a more familiar
   order identifier.
   -

   Improves consistency between customer-facing communications and
   operational workflows.



Enhanced Package Code Visibility in Rider App

The Rider App experience has been enhanced to provide riders with clearer
and more accessible package identification details during order handling
and delivery operations.




Key Updates

   -

   Package-related information is now presented in a more structured and
   readable format within the package details view.
   -

   Key order identifiers are surfaced alongside package information, making
   it easier for riders to validate and identify packages during pickups an=
d
   deliveries.
   -

   Reduced dependency on multiple order references to verify packages.



Ignore Allocation to Blacklisted Riders


The system now supports excluding blacklisted riders from allocation.
Earlier, the riders received the orders and then led to cancellations. This
was confusing and led to improper behaviour for riders.



Now the system ensures that the order is only sent to riders who are
eligible for executing the orders leading to no confusion and proper
allocation.


What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
